Package io.smudgr.api.commands

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AppPort
    Get the current listening port of the WebSocket API
    CanvasPort
    Get the current listening port of the Canvas streaming WebSocket.
    ControlPause
    Pause execution of the current application instance.
    ControlPlay
    Continue execution of the current application instance.
    ControlRecord
    Toggle recording frames to the specified output.
    ControlSaveFrame
    Capture and save the most recent PixelFrame.
    FileList
    Gets a list of files and folders in a given path.
    FileWorkingDirectory
    Gets the current working directory of the smudgr process.
    ParameterSet
    Set the current value of a specified parameter.
    PerformanceFPS
    Gets the current rate the Project.getRack() is rendering at.
    ProjectGet
    Get the project model as a serialized nested JSON object.
    ProjectNew
    Create a new project and load it to the current application instance.
    ProjectOpen
    Open a project file and load it to the current application instance.
    ProjectSave
    Save current project to user specified location.
    RackGet
    Get a specific rack model as a serialized nested JSON object.
    RackSmudgeAdd
    Add a Smudge to a Rack in the current Project.
    RackSmudgeMove
    Take the Smudge at the fromIndex and insert it at the toIndex
    RackSmudgeRemove
    Remove the Smudge with the given ID from the current Rack
    SmudgeComponentAdd
    Add a SmudgeComponent to a Smudge in the current Project.
    SmudgeComponentMove
    Take the SmudgeComponent at the fromIndex and insert it at the toIndex
    SmudgeComponentRemove
    Remove a SmudgeComponent from its parent Smudge and the current Project.
    SmudgeGet
    Get a specific smudge model as a serialized nested JSON object.
    SourceCurrentSet
    Set the current source with an ID
    SourceLibraryGet
    Gets a list of source sets and sources contained in them.
    SourceThumbnail
    Gets a thumbnail preview of a given source
    TypesSmudge
    Gets available smudge types, as identifiers and display names
    TypesSmudgeComponent
    Gets available smudge component types for a particular smudge type, as identifiers and display names
